# Task Manager (MERN Stack)

A simple full-stack Task Manager application built using the MERN stack. The app allows users to create, view, update, and delete tasks. It demonstrates basic CRUD operations with a React frontend and a Node.js + Express backend connected to MongoDB.

## Features

* Add new tasks
* View all tasks
* Mark tasks as completed
* Delete tasks
* Responsive UI
* REST API integration

## Tech Stack

Frontend

* React
* Axios
* CSS

Backend

* Node.js
* Express.js
* MongoDB
* Mongoose

Tools

* Git & GitHub

## Project Structure

```
task-manager-mern
│
├── backend
│   ├── models
│   ├── routes
│   ├── server.js
│   └── .env
│
└── Frontend
    ├── src
    ├── public
    └── package.json
```

## Installation

Clone the repository

```
git clone https://github.com/vijaydev-07/task-manager-mern.git
```

Go to the project folder

```
cd task-manager-mern
```

### Backend Setup

```
cd backend
npm install
```

Create a `.env` file

```
PORT=5000
MONGO_URI=your_mongodb_connection_string
```

Run the backend

```
npm start
```

### Frontend Setup

Open a new terminal

```
cd Frontend
npm install
npm run dev
```

## API Endpoint

```
GET     /api/tasks
POST    /api/tasks
PUT     /api/tasks/:id
DELETE  /api/tasks/:id
```

